The paper discusses the security and reliability of biometric template protection schemes, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also analyzes the distance correlation characteristic of cancelable biometrics, which involves mathematical and statistical analysis, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.MM), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG).
